 display a specific DateTime format in a DevExpress dxg:GridControl, you can modify the display format for a particular dxg:GridColumn. This can be done directly in the XAML by setting the column's EditSettings to a DateEditSettings and specifying the desired format. Here's how you can do it:

Using XAML (Preferred)
xml
코드 복사
<dxg:GridControl ItemsSource="{Binding YourDataSource}">
    <dxg:GridControl.Columns>
        <!-- Other columns -->
        
        <dxg:GridColumn FieldName="time123" Header="Time">
            <dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
                <dxe:DateEditSettings DisplayFormat="yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" />
            </dxg:GridColumn.EditSettings>
        </dxg:GridColumn>
        
    </dxg:GridControl.Columns>
</dxg:GridControl>
Explanation:
The FieldName is bound to your data source's DateTime property (time123).
DisplayFormat="yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss" specifies the desired display format.
Using Code-Behind
If you prefer setting the format programmatically in the code-behind, you can use the following:

csharp
코드 복사
using DevExpress.Xpf.Editors.Settings;

var column = new GridColumn
{
    FieldName = "time123",
    Header = "Time",
    EditSettings = new DateEditSettings
    {
        DisplayFormat = "yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss"
    }
};

yourGridControl.Columns.Add(column);
Replace yourGridControl with the name of your GridControl.
This approach dynamically adds the column and sets the DateTime format.
Using DataTemplate (Alternative Approach)
If you need more customization or cannot use EditSettings, you can use a CellTemplate:

xml
코드 복사
<dxg:GridControl ItemsSource="{Binding YourDataSource}">
    <dxg:GridControl.Columns>
        <!-- Other columns -->
        
        <dxg:GridColumn FieldName="time123" Header="Time">
            <dxg:GridColumn.CellTemplate>
                <DataTemplate>
                    <TextBlock Text="{Binding time123, StringFormat=yy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss}" />
                </DataTemplate>
            </dxg:GridColumn.CellTemplate>
        </dxg:GridColumn>
        
    </dxg:GridControl.Columns>
</dxg:GridControl>
Explanation:
StringFormat is applied to the Text property of the TextBlock in the DataTemplate.
Recommendations
Preferred Method: Use the EditSettings approach for simplicity and built-in support.